# =============================================================================
# ROOT .env.example - INDEX ONLY
# =============================================================================
# This repo does not load one shared root .env for the apps.
#
# Copy the example that sits next to the app/package you want to run:
#
#   cp apps/web/.env.example          apps/web/.env.local
#   cp apps/admin/.env.example        apps/admin/.env.local
#   cp apps/super-admin/.env.example  apps/super-admin/.env.local
#   cp apps/svc-roadmap/.env.example  apps/svc-roadmap/.env
#   cp packages/db/.env.example       packages/db/.env
#
# Next.js apps read .env.local. svc-roadmap and packages/db read .env.
# Real secrets stay only in gitignored files and hosting dashboards.
#
# Full guide: docs/onboarding/env.md
# =============================================================================

# Key sources, in short:
# - Clerk:  https://dashboard.clerk.com -> your app -> API Keys
# - Clerk webhooks: Clerk app -> Webhooks -> endpoint -> Signing Secret
# - Database: dev uses SQLite file:./dev.db; prod uses Postgres/Neon
# - Sentry: https://sentry.io -> project -> Settings -> Client Keys (DSN)
#
# The root .env, when present, is only for local tooling that explicitly reads it.
# It is not the source of truth for any workspace app.
